@page "/about"
<h1>About PrTask</h1>
<p>PrTask is a platform where developers earn money by submitting pull requests to real projects.</p>
<section class="about-section">
    <h2>What We Do</h2>
    <p>Clients post development tasks with bounties. Developers claim tasks, write code, and submit pull requests. Once a PR is reviewed, approved, and merged, the developer gets paid based on the complexity of their work.</p>
</section>
<section class="about-section">
    <h2>Game-Like Experience</h2>
    <p>Every merged PR earns XP based on complexity scoring. Level up, unlock achievement badges, and maintain streaks for bonus multipliers. Compete on the public leaderboard. All pull requests are public.</p>
</section>
<section class="about-section">
    <h2>Secure Payments</h2>
    <p>Client bounty payments are processed via supported payment providers. When a client approves a pull request, they are automatically charged and the developer gets paid. No upfront deposit required. Developers choose their preferred payout method.</p>
</section>
